---
@META
dir: argocd
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 6
stack: ArgoCD, Kubernetes, SealedSecrets

@EXPORTS
application.yaml: ArgoCD Application — GitOps app definition pointing to helm/ chart
values-staging.yaml: config — Helm values override for staging environment
values-production.yaml: config — Helm values override for production environment
harbor-registry-sealed-secret.yaml: SealedSecret — Harbor container registry credentials
postgres-sealed-secret.yaml: SealedSecret — PostgreSQL connection credentials
ucebnice-sealed-secret.yaml: SealedSecret — app environment secrets (NEXTAUTH, etc.)

@PROCESSES
GitOps: push to main → ArgoCD detects change → syncs helm chart with values → K8s rollout
SealedSecrets: create-sealed-secrets.sh → kubeseal → commit encrypted secrets to Git

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: helm/ucebnice (referenced by application.yaml)
external: ArgoCD, kubeseal, Harbor registry

@STANDARDS
- SealedSecrets for GitOps-safe secret management
- Separate values files for staging vs production
- ArgoCD auto-sync enabled

@WARNINGS
- SealedSecrets are cluster-specific — cannot be decrypted outside target cluster
- Harbor robot account credentials in sealed secret
---
